  <note>
    <title>Fat necrosis</title>
    <created>20180719T054314Z</created>
    <updated>20191023T044620Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Fat necrosis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows fat necrosis with aggregates of foamy histiocytes and focal lymphocytic infiltration.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180830T013721Z</created>
    <updated>20180830T013743Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>https://www.google.com.tw/search?q=VATS+pericardial+window&amp;rlz=1C1BEMX_zh-TWTW773TW773&amp;oq=VATS+pericardial+window&amp;aqs=chrome..69i57j0l3.362j0j7&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Fibrinous pericarditis/pleuritis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic descriptions:</div><div>Section shows fibrinous exudates on pericardial surface,</div><div>accompanied by orderly arrangement of vessels.</div><div>Immunohistochemically, CD68 highlights scattered histiocytes</div><div>without granuloma formation. No mycobacterial microorganisms</div><div>are identified by acid fast stain or TB immunostain. No</div><div>malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>hemostatic agents (gelfoam)</title>
    <created>20190301T095821Z</created>
    <updated>20250502T061535Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Some foreign body-like materials are seen, probably representing hemostatic agents of previous surgery.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
