  <note>
    <title>Ki-67 membranous staining</title>
    <created>20170118T075328Z</created>
    <updated>20170118T075344Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Staining for Ki-67 shows an intense membranous staining, which is considered a cross-reactivity of the MIB-1 monoclonal antibody with an epitope expressed at the cell membrane level. The result is not significant and is not contributory to evaluating Ki-67 labeling index of the tumor. </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>LEL-like carcinoma</title>
    <created>20170111T130350Z</created>
    <updated>20170111T130445Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows _ tissue replaced by a dense infiltrate of lymphoplasmacytic cells with occasional more prominent neutrophils. Interspersed within the inflammation are small nests and cords of cohesive clusters as well as individual cells containing large nuclei with multiple nucleoli, abundant eosinophilic to amphophilic cytoplasm and frequent mitoses.<br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Lymph nodes 同一顆</title>
    <created>20251008T054703Z</created>
    <updated>20251008T054730Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div>（A15 and A16 each represent a single lymph node that has been sectioned into multiple pieces)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>melanocytic lesion 建議 excisional or large incisional biopsy</title>
    <created>20210531T011553Z</created>
    <updated>20210531T011710Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Preferably excisional or large incisional biopsy</div><div><br/></div><div>Important to visualize peripheral edges and deeper aspects of the tumor to comment on circumscription and maturation</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Non-diagnostic due to cautery artifact</title>
    <created>20251021T021222Z</created>
    <updated>20251021T021334Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div>Non-diagnostic due to cautery artifact.</div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The section shows squamous-lined tissue with severe cautery artifact. Due to the extent of the artifact, histological details are poorly preserved, and a definitive diagnosis cannot be made.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
