  <note>
    <title>Soft tissue &amp; Bone</title>
    <created>20140802T005924Z</created>
    <updated>20171212T061742Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">C/W calcium pyrophosphate dihydrate crystal deposition disease, right thigh 2015060697</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">C/W osteophyte</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows cartilage and bony spicules consistent with osteophytes. No malignancy is observed.</span></div></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Gangrene and osteomyelitis</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section of the skin and soft tissues show liquefactive necrosis with heavy PMNs infiltration as well as lymphoplasmacytic cells infiltration in the adjacent viable tissue. There are also necrotic bony chips with neutrophilic infiltrate and fibrosis.</span></div><div><br/></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br/></div></div><div>Cavernous intramuscular hemangioma</div><div style="margin-left: 40px;">Section shows ectatic thin-walled vascular spaces infiltrating within degenerating skeletal muscle, accompanied by intravascular thrombosis. No malignancy is observed.</div><div style="margin-left: 40px;"><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Thrombosis</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows a dilated thin-walled vessel containing blood and fibrin clots in the lumen in the submucosa. No malignancy is noted.</span></div><div><br/></div></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Neurofibroma</span></div><div>Sections show multiple lesions composed of bland-looking spindle cells revealing wavy</div><div>nuclei admixed with collagen bundles and focal myxoid background.</div><div>Immunohistochemically, the  </div><div>Section shows dermal tumor composed of loosely-arranged spindle shape</div><div>cells with round and comma-shaped nuclei with fine and delicate</div><div>collagen.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><br clear="none" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SSTR report</title>
    <created>20250320T094432Z</created>
    <updated>20250321T021706Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>SSTR2a: _% positive tumor cells with weak/moderate/strong staining intensity.</div><div>SSTR5: _% positive tumor cells with weak/moderate/strong staining intensity.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><a href="evernote:///view/26224745/s227/5a683fe7-538f-568b-ae14-0964686d2b20/7c4a906a-3784-41ae-a00c-cb1da4284fc5" rev="en_rl_none">SSTR2A</a></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SUPP1 Acute suppurative inflammation</title>
    <created>20170618T041114Z</created>
    <updated>20241111T073316Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>suppurative inflammation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows suppurative inflammation with collections of neutrophils, liquified debris of necrotic cells and edema fluid.     </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180809T084650Z</created>
    <updated>20180809T084650Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(4, 51, 255); font-family: gotham;">Synchronous - simultaneously</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(4, 51, 255); font-family: gotham;">Metachronous - one after the other</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">The immunostains may not be optimal due to acid decalcification. 脫鈣染色不準i</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">induration 硬化</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">......with a</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(188, 0, 88); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Ki-67</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">nuclear labeling index of approximately _%. </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Spontaneous expulsion 病人自行排出</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Contiguous spread</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Mucocutaneous tissue</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">There is no finding  suggestive of cancer in this limited specimen.(檢體太小)</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Atypical glands that are suspicious but not diagnostic of carcinoma. <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(153, 51, 0);">(怪怪的但打不到CA)</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(153, 51, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Lesion被Biopsy 切掉了： </span><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: gotham;">We have reviewed the prior needle core biopsy and agree that there is ....</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: gotham;">This lesion appears to have been entirely removed with core biopsy sampling.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(153, 51, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">"Atypical glands suspicious</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(153, 51, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; text-decoration: underline;">of</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(153, 51, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">malignancy" </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">There are invasive carcinoma present on the</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(153, 51, 0);">crushed inferior margin <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">where the overlying mucosa is uninvolved (Crushed 的margin有tumor)</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(153, 51, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">The morphologic findings are suspicious for but not diagnostic of ......</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">The specimen reveals serious</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(255, 102, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">crushing artifact,</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">which limits a proper pathologic evaluation of the cytologic details.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">cauterization artifact</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Regenerative atypia</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Final tumor staging will be determined by total excisional specimen</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(153, 51, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">對外consult, 結果加在addendum.</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">This case is sent to Dr. Huang HY at Kaohsiung CGMH for further consultation for subtyping of RCC. The result of the consultation will be reported as addendum.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">The overall staining results exclude carcinoma or lymphoma, and are compatible with a _.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">arTangential cut 斜切</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Sections from different levels show 翻面切</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">These findings are consistent but not</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(255, 102, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">pathognomonic</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">for ulcerative colitis.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">aberrant loss</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">再切就沒了: This tiny focus</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(153, 51, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">is exhausted out in further sections</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">for CD68 and TTF-1</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">immunostains.</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">involved and cauterized</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">enclose 圍住</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">elastosis: </span><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight: bold;"> </span><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">degenerative changes in the dermal connective tissue with increased amounts of elastotic material.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Reparative reaction: 修復</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Overt 明顯</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">, interspersed with.....(散在的)</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">cigar-shaped: smooth muscle 平行, 兩頭鈍鈍的</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">intersecting:相交叉</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">jastaposed 緊黏</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">exfoliated 片狀剝落的</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">scanty 缺乏</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">closely-packed</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">bumpy 崎嶇不平</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Leukoplakia , keratosis(oral cavity)</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">devoid of 沒有 </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">dimpling 凹陷 (nipple)</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">discern 分辨; 看出 </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">desmoplastic reaction: growth of fibrous or connective tissue.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">infestation  </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: small; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: left; color: rgb(221, 75, 57); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal;">Acantholysis</span><span style="text-align: left; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 12px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> is the loss of intercellular connections, such as desmosomes</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Parakeratosis:retention of nuclei in the stratum corneum</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">infestation: 寄生蟲侵擾</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Organoid: 中間有類似紅紅的collagen隔開形成一簌一簌的樣子</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(255, 102, 0);">Oncocytic cells</span>: having abundant pink granular cytoplasm (due to lots of mitochondria) and</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">bland small round nuclei</span></div></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(255, 38, 0); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Cytologic system</span></div><ul style="margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><span style="font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">GX Grade cannot be assessed</span></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><span style="font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">G1 Well differentiated (Low grade)</span></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><span style="font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">G2 Moderately differentiated (Intermediate grade)</span></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><span style="font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">G3 Poorly differentiated (High grade)</span></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><span style="font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">G4 Undifferentiated (High grade)</span></li></ul><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">In</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(35, 146, 28); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight: bold;">caseous necrosis</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> (caseating)  histological architecture is  reserved. Acellular pink areas of necrosis surrounded by a </span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Granuloma" shape="rect" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;" target="_blank" title="Granuloma">granulomatous</a><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> inflammatory process.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">  - foci of </span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuberculosis" shape="rect" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;" target="_blank" title="Tuberculosis">tuberculous</a><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> infections.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(51, 153, 102); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight: bold;">liquefactive necrosis: </span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">dead cells are</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(0, 0, 255); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">completely digested away</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">and normal architecture is obliterated. Usually caused by</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; text-decoration: underline;">infection</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">and is associated with inflammatory cells.</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Ulceration = neutrophil + necrotic debris + vessel</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Angiofibroma growth pattern</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(255, 102, 0);">Granulative tissue</span>: edematous stroma and small vessel (increased vascularity)</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(255, 102, 0);">Granuloma</span> = rounded aggregate of histiocytes. Histiocytes in a granuloma have abundant cytoplasm (are “epithelioid”) and indistinct cell borders such that they seem to merge into a </span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">                     syncytium. Giant cells are usually but not always present. If syncytial aggregates of histiocytes/giant cells are in sheets (rather than in a discreet nodule) the preferred term is                                          “granulomatous inflammation” rather than granuloma.</span></div><div style="margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">quick reference <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: italic; text-decoration: underline;">p177</span></span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Fibrinopurulent</span></div></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;">Hobnail</span>-> yolk sac tumor, ovary clear cell ca</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">PECOMA: can occult in lung(LAM)) , kidney, uterus</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Sunburst</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><en-media hash="158704d6dcfda3ba6a88896f13e1f6bd" style="height: auto;" type="image/jpeg" /></span></div></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
