  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180628T021020Z</created>
    <updated>20230918T025318Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>This case had been sent to Dr. Kung-Chao Chang at</div><div>National Cheng Kung University Hospital for consultation. His comment is described as follows:</div><div><br/></div><div>PATHOLOGICAL DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Lymph node (?), left axillary, core biopsy --- Anaplastic large cell lymphoma, ALK-negative (See Note).</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Section reveals sheets of atypical lymphoid cells with</div><div>prominent necrosis. These atypical lymphoid cells are</div><div>medium- or large-sized with irregular nuclei and focal</div><div>multinucleation. Focally eccentric kidney-shaped nuclei are</div><div>present.</div><div><br/></div><div>By immunohistochemistry, the tumor cells are diffusely</div><div>positive for CD3 and CD30 but not CD20 or AE1/AE3. In situ</div><div>hybridization for EBV-encoded mRNA (EBER) is focally</div><div>positive.</div><div><br/></div><div>We also performed 9 immunostains including LCA, CD20, CD43,</div><div>EMA, CD4, granzyme B, ALK, TIA1 &amp; bF-1 (18C00200).</div><div><br/></div><div>Note: The differential is CD30-positive peripheral T-cell lymphoma NOS. In view of morphology and EMA+/betaF-1(-), ALK-negative ALCL is favored.</div><div>---------------------------------------------------------</div><div>PRELIMINARY DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Lymph node, left axilla, core biopsy --- T-cell lymphoma</div><div><br/></div><div>Note: This case will be sent to Dr. Kung-Chao Chang at</div><div>National Cheng Kung University Hospital for further</div><div>consultation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of 7 pieces of tissue measuring</div><div>up to 0.7x0.1x0.1 cm.</div><div>All for section.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section reveals sheets of atypical lymphoid cells with</div><div>prominent necrosis. These atypical lymphoid cells are</div><div>medium- or large-sized with irregular nuclei and focal</div><div>multinucleation. Focally eccentric kidney-shaped nuclei are</div><div>present.</div><div><br/></div><div>By immunohistochemistry, the tumor cells are diffusely</div><div>positive for CD3 and CD30 but not CD20 or AE1/AE3. In situ</div><div>hybridization for EBV-encoded mRNA (EBER) is focally</div><div>positive.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20220414T081627Z</created>
    <updated>20230830T050434Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>thrombosed graft with suppurative inflammation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show graft material with fibrin thrombi and suppurative inflammation with collections of</div><div>neutrophils, liquified debris of necrotic cells and edema</div><div>fluid. Foreign body reaction is seen.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>TROP-2 report</title>
    <created>20240315T030136Z</created>
    <updated>20250320T094433Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>mobile.iphone</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>TROP-2: _% positive tumor cells with weak/moderate/strong staining intensity.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><a href="evernote:///view/26224745/s227/c555ff8d-8136-b3b0-854a-a1d531ab3b30/7c4a906a-3784-41ae-a00c-cb1da4284fc5" rev="en_rl_none">TROP-2</a></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>tumor 太少 suspicious/ 無法分類</title>
    <created>20241112T025236Z</created>
    <updated>20241112T025333Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>There are too few viable tumor cells, and while malignancy is suspected, no further information can be provided.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Words and phrases</title>
    <created>20130812T070255Z</created>
    <updated>20231006T042000Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Margins, separately excised specimens</span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(4, 51, 255);">side not stated (沒寫哪一邊）</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(4, 51, 255);">Synchronous - simultaneously</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(4, 51, 255);">Metachronous - one after the other</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The immunostains may not be optimal due to acid decalcification. 脫鈣染色不準</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">induration 硬化</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">......with a</span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(188, 0, 88);">Ki-67</span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">nuclear labeling index of approximately _%. </span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Spontaneous expulsion 病人自行排出</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Contiguous spread</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Mucocutaneous tissue</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">There is no finding  suggestive of cancer in this limited specimen.(檢體太小)</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Atypical glands that are suspicio    us but not diagnostic of carcinoma. <span style="color:rgb(153, 51, 0);">(怪怪的但打不到CA)</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(153, 51, 0);">Lesion被Biopsy 切掉了： </span></span></span><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">We have reviewed the prior needle core biopsy and agree that there is ....</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">This lesion appears to have been entirely removed with core biopsy sampling.</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(153, 51, 0);">"Atypical glands suspicious</span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(153, 51, 0);"><u>of</u></span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(153, 51, 0);">malignancy" </span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">There are invasive carcinoma present on the</span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(153, 51, 0);">crushed inferior margin</span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">where the overlying mucosa is uninvolved (Crushed 的margin有tumor)</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(153, 51, 0);">The morphologic findings are suspicious for but not diagnostic of ......</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The specimen reveals serious</span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(255, 102, 0);">crushing artifact,</span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">which limits a proper pathologic evaluation of the cytologic details.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">cauterization artifact</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Regenerative atypia</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Final tumor staging will be determined by total excisional specimen</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(153, 51, 0);">對外consult, 結果加在addendum.</span></span></span></div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">This case is sent to Dr. Huang HY at Kaohsiung CGMH for further consultation for subtyping of RCC. The result of the consultation will be reported as addendum.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The overall staining results exclude carcinoma or lymphoma, and are compatible with a _.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">arTangential cut 斜切</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Sections from different levels show 翻面切</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">These findings are consistent but not</span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(255, 102, 0);">pathognomonic</span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">for ulcerative colitis.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">aberrant loss</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">再切就沒了: This tiny focus</span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(153, 51, 0);">is exhausted out in further sections</span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">for CD68 and TTF-1</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">This small focus is further </span></span><b><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(209, 0, 255);">exhausted</span></span></span></b><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> in the following sections for p40 and p16 immunostains.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">immunostains.</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">involved and cauterized</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">enclose 圍住</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">elastosis: </span></span></span><b><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span></span></span></b><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">degenerative changes in the dermal connective tissue with increased amounts of elastotic material.</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Reparative reaction: 修復</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Overt 明顯</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">, interspersed with.....(散在的)</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">cigar-shaped: smooth muscle 平行, 兩頭鈍鈍的</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">intersecting:相交叉</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">jastaposed 緊黏</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">exfoliated 片狀剝落的</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">scanty 缺乏</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">closely-packed</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">bumpy 崎嶇不平</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Leukoplakia , keratosis(oral cavity)</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">devoid of 沒有 </span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">dimpling 凹陷 (nipple)</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">discern 分辨; 看出 </span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">desmoplastic reaction: growth of fibrous or connective tissue.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">infestation  </span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(221, 75, 57);">Acantholysis</span></span></span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(68, 68, 68);"> is the loss of intercellular connections, such as desmosomes</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Parakeratosis:retention of nuclei in the stratum corneum</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">infestation: 寄生蟲侵擾</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Organoid: 中間有類似紅紅的collagen隔開形成一簌一簌的樣子</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(255, 102, 0);">Oncocytic cells</span>: having abundant pink granular cytoplasm (due to lots of mitochondria) and</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">bland small round nuclei</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(255, 38, 0);">Cytologic system</span></span></span></div><ul><li><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">GX Grade cannot be assessed</span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">G1 Well differentiated (Low grade)</span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">G2 Moderately differentiated (Intermediate grade)</span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">G3 Poorly differentiated (High grade)</span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">G4 Undifferentiated (High grade)</span></span></div></li></ul><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">In</span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><b><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(35, 146, 28);">caseous necrosis</span></span></span></b><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> (caseating)  histological architecture is  reserved. Acellular pink areas of necrosis surrounded by a <a title="Granuloma" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Granuloma" rev="en_rl_none" shape="rect" target="_blank">granulomatous</a> inflammatory process.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">  - foci of <a title="Tuberculosis" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuberculosis" rev="en_rl_none" shape="rect" target="_blank">tuberculous</a> infections.</span></span></div><div><b><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(51, 153, 102);">liquefactive necrosis: </span></span></span></b><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">dead cells are</span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 255);">completely digested away</span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">and normal architecture is obliterated. Usually caused by</span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(51, 102, 255);"><u>infection</u></span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">and is associated with inflammatory cells.</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Ulceration = neutrophil + necrotic debris + vessel</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Angiofibroma growth pattern</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(255, 102, 0);">Granulative tissue</span>: edematous stroma and small vessel (increased vascularity)</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(255, 102, 0);">Granuloma</span> = rounded aggregate of histiocytes. Histiocytes in a granuloma have abundant cytoplasm (are “epithelioid”) and indistinct cell borders such that they seem to merge into a </span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">                     syncytium. Giant cells are usually but not always present. If syncytial aggregates of histiocytes/giant cells are in sheets (rather than in a discreet nodule) the preferred term is                                          “granulomatous inflammation” rather than granuloma.</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">quick reference <i><u>p177</u></i></span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Fibrinopurulent</span></span></div><div><b><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(255, 0, 0);">Hobnail</span></span></span></b><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">-> yolk sac tumor, ovary clear cell ca</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">PECOMA: can occult in lung(LAM)) , kidney, uterus</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Sunburst</span></span></div><div><br/></div><en-media style="--en-naturalWidth:750; --en-naturalHeight:553;" height="autopx" hash="158704d6dcfda3ba6a88896f13e1f6bd" type="image/jpeg" /><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
