  <note>
    <title>再切就沒了 再切就不見了 切完了</title>
    <created>20230802T133309Z</created>
    <updated>20241204T021410Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="color:rgb(102, 102, 102);">Because the lesions are small, they are cut out in deeper levels or subsequent immunohistochemistry.</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div>disappearance on step levels</div><div><br/></div><div>but disappear on subsequent step levels in PAS staining.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>原本報告由．．．發出</title>
    <created>20240102T030059Z</created>
    <updated>20240102T030821Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The orginal report, signed by Dr. Tsung-Han Teng, was issued on December 12, 2023.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>垃圾報告_Form</title>
    <created>20140618T030927Z</created>
    <updated>20230825T082311Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">SFT42-ST necrotizing inflammation</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Callus, skin (2014-12-2752)</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">CHR NSD</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">CPS</span></div></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">1. Section of the turbinates reveal marked stromal edema, vascular proliferation and glandular hyperplasia as well as lymphocytic and eosinophilic cells infiltration.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">No evidence of malignancy.</span></div></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Strip of hyaline cartilage is consistent with septal cartilage.</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> 2. The sinus mucosal shows glandular proliferation, marked stromal edema, lymphocytic and eosinophilic inflammation. No evidence of malignancy.</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Chronic active gastritis with/without HP STO14/STO15</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">C/W urachal fistula</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows skin and subcutaneous fibrous tissue with fistulous tract and several congested vessels. Chronic active inflammation is present. No evidence of malignancy is discerned.</span></div></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">(Ptosis) Confirmed, right eyelid, levator muscle resection/levator aponeurosis tucking</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows fragments of skin and muscular tissue. No evidence of malignancy is observed.</span></div></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Chronic otitis media</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">The covering epithelium is unremarkable, while the underlying fibrous tissue shows marked inflammatory cell infiltration, fibrosis and vascular dilation.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Chronic otitis media with cholesteatoma, right middle ear, tympanoplasty with mastoidectomy</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">The section shows soft tissue with chronic inflammation and laminated keratin consistent with chronic otitis media with cholesteatoma.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Chronic hypertrophic tonsillitis </span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Degenerated fibrous tissue, left inguinal area, orchiopexy</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">It shows fibroadipose tissue with degeneration. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Consistent with entropion, right eye, Hotz's operation 2015062336</span></div></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows umremarkable skeletal muscle tissue only. No evidence of malignancy.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Osteoarthritis, left knee, total knee replacement</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">The decalcified specimen shows damaged articular cartilage with partial destruction of</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">the cortical bone which is replaced by fibrovascular tissue and cartilage. The bony</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">trabeculae are unremarkable and so are the marrow spaces.</span></div></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Retention polyp</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows a retention polyp with variably and cystically dilated glands within the lamina propria of the mucosa, giving rise to a swiss-cheese appearance. These glands are partially filled with mucinous material and which are widely separated by abundant stroma. No evidence of malignancy is noted.</span></div></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Phimosis (with balanitis), prepuce, circumcision</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Paronychia </span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Pterygium, eye </span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows conjunctival tissue with elastotic degeneration of collagen fibrovascular proliferation and hemorrhage.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Consistent with orchiopexy for undescended testis, left inguinal, orchiopexy</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">It shows fibromuscular tissue fragments, consistent with orchiopexy.</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Consistent with orchiopexy for undescended testis, left inguinal, orchiopexy</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">It shows fibromuscular tissue fragments, consistent with orchiopexy.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Hernical sac</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">It is a saccular lesion composed of loose fibrous connective tissue.</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><br/></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Varicose veins 2015031685</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><ol><li><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Chronic inflammation, appendix epididymis, biopsy</span></div></li><li><div>Sac, left hydrocele, hydrocelectomy</div></li><ul><li><div>Section shows chronic inflammation and no evidence of malignancy.</div></li><li><div>It is a saccular lesion composed of loose fibrous connective tissue.</div><div><br clear="none" /></div></li></ul></ol><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><br clear="none" /></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><br clear="none" /></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><br clear="none" /></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><br clear="none" /></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><br clear="none" /></div><div style="margin-left: 30px;"><br clear="none" /></div></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>大件才能給完整診斷</title>
    <created>20240625T044920Z</created>
    <updated>20240625T044947Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>A definite diagnosis can only be made on the subsequent larger specimen.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>如果都排除了  那可以符合</title>
    <created>20240412T072802Z</created>
    <updated>20240412T072826Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>COMMENT:</div><div>Hepatocellular carcinoma, and metastatic colorectal are</div><div>excluded by morphology and immunostains.</div><div><br/></div><div>The immunophenotype suggests metastatic carcinoma, with</div><div>possible origins including mammary, urothelial, or salivary</div><div>duct carcinoma based on positive immunostains with GATA3 and</div><div>TRPS1.</div><div><br/></div><div>However, a small proportion of primary non-small cell lung</div><div>carcinomas also express GATA3 and TRPS1, so a pulmonmary</div><div>origin is possible if no tumors are found in the above-</div><div>mentioned organs. Clinico-radiological correlation is</div><div>recommended for determining the origin of the tumor.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>委外諮詢</title>
    <created>20160826T031902Z</created>
    <updated>20250423T025223Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source-url>https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/#inbox?compose=15c1a434f22b43ea</source-url>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><h3 style="--en-nodeId:e79df028-d849-4804-9fcf-28ece50b9769;">張孔昭教授</h3><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">This case had been sent to Dr. Kung-Chao Chang at National Cheng Kung University</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">Hospital for further consultation. His comment is described as follows:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">(Incorporated with the bone marrow biopsy diagnosis)</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><s>This case had been sent to Dr. Kung-Chao Chang at Kaohsiung Medical University Chung-Ho Memorial Hospital for further consultation.    </s></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><s><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></s></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><s><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></s></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">This case (both the present slide and the previous biopsy slide 201_) had been  sent to Dr. _ at __ HOSPITAL for further consultation. His/her opinion  is as below (DIAGNOSIS and MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION)</span></div><div><br/></div><div>黃玄贏</div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">This case had been sent to Dr. Huang Hsuan-Ying at Kaohsiung CGMH for consultation. His comment is described as below.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">Professor Ho, Ming-Tak at Taipei Veterans General Hospital</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">This case had been sent to Dr.Ying-Tai Jin at Taiwan Adventist Hospital for further consultation. His comment is described as follows:</span></div><div><br/></div><div>謝明書</div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">This case had been sent to Dr.Min-Shu Hsieh at National Taiwan University Hospital for further consultation.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">Dr.Min-Shu Hsieh, and Dr.Yuh-Fang Chang, pathologists in NUTH,</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(166, 0, 196);"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(235, 0, 115);">Dr. 王任卿</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">This case had been sent to Dr. Ren-Ching Wang at Taichung</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">Veterans General Hospital for further consultation.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(235, 0, 115);">Dr. 蕭正祥</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">This case had been sent to Dr. Cheng-Hsiang Hsiao at CHENG HSIN hospital for consultation.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><h3 style="--en-nodeId:74b40784-dec4-4348-aae6-0329ea2efd53;">奇美Dr 莊</h3><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">This case had been sent to</span> <span style="font-size: 9pt;">Dr. Shih-Sung Chuang at Chi-Mei Medical Center for further consultation. </span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">黃士強</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">This case had been sent to</span> <span style="font-size: 9pt;">Dr.</span> <span style="font-size: 9pt;">Shih-Chiang Huang at</span> <span style="font-size: 9pt;">Chang Gung Memorial Hospital for further consultation. </span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">賴理事長</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;">This case had been sent to Dr. Chiung-Ru Lai at Taipei Veterans General Hospital for further consultation.</span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>檢體太小無法評估</title>
    <created>20170305T130844Z</created>
    <updated>20170305T140702Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>However, the specimen is limited and may be not representative for the whole lesion (145.5mm). A large excision / resection specimen is recommended for a more definitive diagnosis.<br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
